- "Either the missing puzzle piece is in the box or it must be blending in on the floor" means that one of these two conditions must be true.
- "The missing puzzle piece might not be blending in on the floor" means that it is possible that the puzzle piece is not blending in on the floor, but it does not rule out the possibility that it is blending in on the floor.
